geller  company names jerry leamon vice chairman of advisory board geller  company names jerry leamon vice chairman of advisory board longtime senior deloitte executive brings nearly  years of experience to geller apr    et from geller  company new york april   prnewswire  geller  company a leading strategic financial advisory firm today announced that jerry p leamon has been named vice chairman of gellers advisory board  mr leamon was until recently global managing director of deloitte one of the worlds largest professional services firm and was a member of the firms senior leadership body  mr leamon will bring his unique and valuable experience to this newly created position as he advises martin geller founder and chief executive officer and the firms senior leadership team on a wide range of business matters  mr leamon and mr geller have a longstanding relationship built over many years of working together on matters in which deloitte and geller have collaborated  mr leamons vast expertise in all of gellers business areas will support the firm as it grows and develops each of its business lines continues to improve its products and services and considers expansion into new areas  the addition of mr leamon follows last months hiring of robert wedeking as chief investment officer of geller family office services gfos further bolstering that business capabilities  martin geller founder and chief executive officer of geller  company commented we are fortunate to have the opportunity to bring an individual of jerry leamons caliber and experience to our organization  jerry is deeply admired in the business community  our company and our clients will benefit significantly from his counsel   mr leamon commented marty and his partners have built an extraordinary firm comprised of highly talented individuals and outstanding clients with a fabulous culture geller has built a terrific reputation for service and quality in their important market offerings  i am excited to help advance the businesses of geller including exploring new opportunities mr leamon served until  as a global managing director of deloitte  he served on deloittes global executive the firms senior leadership body for  years  he also served for  years on the board of directors of deloitte touche tohmatsu limited the firms global organization and for six years on the board of directors of deloittes us member firm over his four decade career with the firm and as a partner for  years mr leamon established a reputation as a leading client service professional with handson experience in the financial services consumer products manufacturing technology media and telecommunications tmt industries  he created and served in a series of new roles and structures with worldwide reach serving as the firstever global managing director of tax  legal services clients  markets with responsibility for overseeing programs directed towards all segments of the firms client portfolio merger  acquisition services and services responsible for leadership and oversight of deloittes core businesses audit tax consulting financial advisory mr leamon served as chair of deloittes global innovation network leading a group of  partners from around the world focused on helping the firm identify and act on emerging client servicerelated issues opportunities and technologies  he was also founder and vice chair of the deloitte center for crossborder investment which promoted a focus on marketplace issues and thought leadership with respect to crossborder investment and transactions wellregarded as a strategist and innovator mr leamon has served in leadership and advisory partner roles for numerous public companies and private clients among the fortune global  and   he has successfully built alliances and joint ventures and achieved extraordinary operating performance in all leadership roles  mr leamon is deeply involved in community affairs and currently serves on the board of directors of americares  about geller  companyfounded in  geller  company is a strategic financial advisory firm that has longstanding relationships with its clients and works closely with them to understand their specific needs and deliver a suite of services across its business segments  the segments include strategic and operational cfo services financial reporting and accounting technology tax advisory services and compliance for corporations partnerships nonprofits and individuals and family office and wealth management services  gellers clients include businesses nonprofits and highnetworth individuals and families the family office and wealth advisory business geller family office services llc gfos with assets under advisement of more than  billion and assets under management in excess of  billion is a registered investment adviser serving wealthy individuals and families and their closely held private and public businesses as well as nonprofits charities and private foundations  by engaging with and carefully listening to its clients gfos helps them determine and implement their goals and objectives through its expertise in the following areas business and personal financial management and reporting retirement and inter and intra generational wealth transfer planning investment management and consolidated reporting tax planning and compliance including trusts and estates through its integrated and executionoriented approach gfos helps its clients achieve their investment cash flow wealth transfer tax and retirement objectives with the highest level of quality and service contact mark semer  daniel yunger kekst and company   source geller  company view table fullscreen view table fullscreen journalists and bloggers the news you need when you need it join pr newswire for journalists to access all of the free services designated to make your job easier in need of subject matter experts for your story submit a free profnet request and find the sources you need learn more dec    et previe